\subsection{\code{KucoinFuturesTrading$add_order_test()}}{
  Place a Test Futures Order (Dry Run)

Validates order parameters without placing a real order. The API performs
all validation checks (balance, symbol, price, etc.) and returns a
simulated order ID. Useful for pre-flight checks in automated systems.
\subsection{Workflow}{
\enumerate{
\item \strong{Build Body}: Constructs JSON body with all non-NULL order parameters (identical to \code{add_order()}).
\item \strong{Request}: Authenticated POST to the test endpoint; no real order is placed.
\item \strong{Parsing}: Returns \code{data.table} with a simulated order ID and client OID.
}
}

\subsection{API Endpoint}{

\verb{POST https://api-futures.kucoin.com/api/v1/orders/test}
}

\subsection{Official Documentation}{

\href{https://www.kucoin.com/docs-new/rest/futures-trading/orders/add-order-test}{KuCoin Add Futures Order Test}

Verified: 2026-05-23
}

