\subsection{\code{KucoinFuturesTrading$add_order_batch()}}{
  Batch Place Futures Orders

Places multiple futures orders in a single API request. Each order in the
batch uses the same parameter structure as \code{add_order()}. The API processes
orders independently; partial failures are possible (some orders may succeed
while others fail).
\subsection{Workflow}{
\enumerate{
\item \strong{Build Body}: Accepts a list of order lists, each containing order parameters.
\item \strong{Request}: Authenticated POST to the batch order endpoint.
\item \strong{Parsing}: Returns \code{data.table} with one row per order result.
}
}

\subsection{API Endpoint}{

\verb{POST https://api-futures.kucoin.com/api/v1/orders/multi}
}

\subsection{Official Documentation}{

\href{https://www.kucoin.com/docs-new/rest/futures-trading/orders/batch-add-orders}{KuCoin Batch Add Futures Orders}

Verified: 2026-05-23
}

\subsection{Automated Trading Usage}{
\itemize{
\item \strong{Grid Trading}: Place multiple limit orders at different price levels in a single request.
\item \strong{Hedging}: Submit simultaneous long and short orders across different symbols.
\item \strong{Efficiency}: Reduce API call overhead by batching orders instead of sending them individually.
}
}

\subsection{curl}{

\if{html}{\out{<div class="sourceCode">}}\preformatted{curl --location --request POST 'https://api-futures.kucoin.com/api/v1/orders/multi' \\
